# Build-context exclusions for the per-service image.
#
# Note on placement: the per-service image must be built with the repo
# root as the build context (so scripts/, packages/, versions.env are
# in scope), which means Docker will not auto-discover this file at
# this path. To make it effective, either:
#
#   - rename it to docker/service/Dockerfile.dockerignore (BuildKit's
#     per-Dockerfile lookup convention), or
#   - mirror these patterns into a .dockerignore at the repo root.
#
# Even when this file is not auto-applied, the COPY commands in
# docker/service/Dockerfile only pull scripts/ and packages/, so
# nothing else can leak into the image regardless. These patterns
# trim the build-context payload sent to the daemon.

# Editor / IDE / VCS droppings
**/.gitkeep
**/.DS_Store
**/.idea
**/.vscode
**/.settings
**/*.swp
**/*.swo
**/Thumbs.db
.git/

# Build outputs (the script regenerates these from source).
dist/

# Not consumed by the per-service image build:
#   - docs/, helm/  ship through other channels
#   - config/       layered in at deploy time, not bake time
#   - tests/        run in the wm-msr-base-test image, not this one
#   - .github/      CI metadata, never baked
docs/
helm/
config/
tests/
.github/
